<DOC><DOCNO> AP890225-0078 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-25-89 1222EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Vietnam-USDoctors     02-25 0209</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Vietnam-US Doctors,0213</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Doctors Operate On 101 Vietnamese Children</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The first U.S. doctors to work inCommunist Vietnam have operated successfully on 101 children, whosuffered mouth deformities, the official Vietnam News Agency saidSaturday.   It said former Prime Minister Pham Van Dong received the doctorsfrom ``Operation Smile'' at the presidential palace in the capital,Hanoi, on Friday and told them he hopes the two countries increasecooperation in medical and other fields.   Seven plastic surgeons and two other physicians corrected cleftlips and palates of children at the Olof Palme Institute for theProtection of Children's Health, said the report, monitored inBangkok.   ``Operation Smile'' is a Norfolk, Va.-based agency and one ofvarious private charitable groups that have responded to a U.S.government call for more humanitarian aid to Hanoi.   The aid call was partly in response to Hanoi's help in resolvingcases of U.S. soldiers missing in the Vietnam War. The Pentagon says2,383 Americans are unaccounted for.   The United States has not established diplomatic relations withVietnam since the communists defeated the U.S.-backed South Vietnamgovernment in April 1975 and reunified the country. However, in thelast two years, more and more private American citizens have visitedVietnam.</TEXT></DOC>